title: results of cts:train will often result in doc id="0"
description:
from this case: https://help.marklogic.com/staff/Tickets/Ticket/View/12425

The given customer test case can semi-reliably reproduce results that have doc id="0" There was a period where my windows install would reliably reproduce the behaviour, but doesn't any longer. After talking it over with Mary, I shifted over to a linux instance, and could get the erroneous results both with and without waiting for the in memory stand to write down to disk before calling cts:train.

Test case exists in my home directory at /home/fsalonga/CASES/OSA/12425/. In qconsole, importing the workspace contained in reproducer-ORIG.xml will present you with two queries: 1) Install and 2) Execute. Invoke them in order and you'll get a result contained in "/reproducer-osa/classifier.xml" that should contain 0 doc ids.

Will attach an archive containing the necessary files after bug is created, as well.

support.headline: Using supports form of classifier on large training sets may produce invalid classifier
support.supportDescription: When using the supports form of the classifier on training sets with more than 1000 documents, sometimes the classifier produced includes document ids of 0, which is not usable.

customerImpact.title: Significant business impact with no reasonable workaround

support.workaround: Use training sets with fewer than 1000 documents, or the weights form of the classifier.

changeHistory.comment: I am assuming we are not dealing with this for 5.0-5.
cloning High impact customer bug to 6.0 branch
Workaround: Keep training sets to under 1000 documents.
